# Anti-Patterns to Avoid

Do not do these:

- mark everything Critical to get attention
- mark everything Minor to avoid conflict
- classify based only on who reported it
- classify based only on visibility
- classify based on fear instead of observed impact
- ignore workaround availability
- ignore data/security/auth/payment risk
- confuse test environment failure with product severity
- treat unclear requirements as confirmed bugs
- downgrade security issues because they are rare
- upgrade cosmetic issues to Critical because stakeholders saw them
- ignore business rules because behavior "looks odd"
- assume root cause without evidence
- file duplicate bugs without checking known defects
- hide uncertainty; use confidence labels

